Creamsicle Icebox Cake

Candied Orange Wheels:
2 oranges, sliced into 1/4" thick wheels
2 c sugar
1 1/2 c water divided + more for blanching

In a large skillet, cover the orange wheels with cold water and bring to a simmer. Cook until the wheels are softened, 10 min. Transfer the wheels to a plate and discard the water. Return the skillet to medium heat and add the sugar and water. Bring to a simmer and stir until the sugar dissolves, 2 min. Add the oranges to the syrup and cook until the wheels are translucent and the syrup has reduced, 40 min. Transfer to a parchment paper lined baking sheet and let cool completely. Reserve 3 tbsp of the syrup.


Ricotta Cream:
32 oz whole milk ricotta
1/2 c sugar
2 tbsp reserved orange syrup
1 tbsp orange zest
1 tsp kosher salt

In a blender, combine all ingredients and puree until smooth, then set aside.


Orange Cream:
6 creamsicles, sticks removed
2 c heavy cream
1 tbsp reserved orange syrup
1/2 tsp kosher salt

In a medium saucepan, melt the creamsicles over medium heat. Bring to a simmer and reduce until a thick sauce has formed, 10-12 min. In a medium bowl, whisk the cream to stiff peaks. Fold in the cooled sauce, 1 tbsp of reserved syrup and salt.

Assembly:
12 c (2x11oz boxes) vanilla wafers
Ricotta Cream
Orange Cream

Line a 9" springform pan with plastic wrap. Cover the bottom surface completely with a single layer of vanilla wafers, followed by half of the reoctta cream, another layer of the wafers, and half ov the orange cream. Repeat one more time using the rest of the wafers and fillings. Cover the top with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2hrs, then transfer to the freezer to freeze overnight. The next day, remove the cake and unwrap the plastic. Transfer to a plate and layer the candied orange slices over the top. Let temper for 10 min, then serve.
